headline: S&P 500 Pulls Back From Record as Bond Yields Rise
summary: The S&P 500 pulled back after crossing its Oct. 28 closing high. The market benchmark was up just 0.2% and losing steam as the morning rolled on. The Dow was up 136 points, or 0.3%. The Nasdaq Composite was up 0.

headline: Vistra Stock: Is VST Outperforming the Utilities Sector?
summary: Vistra has outperformed the broader utilities sector over the past year, and analysts remain strongly bullish on the stock’s prospects.

headline: BMO Launches New CDRs With Exposure to U.S. Stocks Including Apollo Global Management, ConocoPhillips, Northrop Grumman, Home Depot and Vistra
summary: Bank of Montreal (BMO) announced five new Canadian depositary receipts (CDRs) will begin trading on the Cboe Canada exchange today. The initial offering of these new CDRs has closed.
